te because it has been discontinued. You can still read about it below, but Top Ten Reviews is no longer updating this product’s information.</em>","The Dropcam Pro security camera provides <a href=\"/best-security-cameras\">video surveillance</a> for an entire room, even if you’re not panning or zooming. The 130-degree field of view is enough for you to capture wall-to-wall footage from the small mount, and you can download the app to stay connected with the live stream via any mobile device. Using the app, you can also flip through the day’s activity, pan and zoom from a remote location, save and share old footage on the cloud, set up a time lapse, and manage and set up custom alerts.","Dropcam’s parent company, Nest, emphasizes the family side of their business and offers cloud storage options to hold onto and share footage with family and friends. We found the cameras to work great as baby or pet monitors, and the two-way talk feature is cool for parents who might want to sing a lullaby to their little one before bed, even if they’re not in the house. The alerts are impressive as well, since you can set up notifications if your front door opens or the baby makes a sound.","The Dropcam Pro comes with a three-megapixel image sensor, with the ability for you to zoom in up to eight times from your chosen device. Using your mobile phone, computer or tablet, you can scan the room or take a closer look at something.","The Dropcam Pro security system wants you to leverage the app as much as possible. Nest has a sharp-looking website that outlines all the benefits of its products and add-ons. The Dropcam itself requires a cord but leverages your Wi-Fi connection to broadcast your stream to whatever devices you’re using the app on.","Nest’s Dropcam Pro security camera isn’t equipped with the weatherproofing protection you see in standard outdoor models. It’s best for setting up on a desk or wall mount indoors."]},"id":"8296289c-b374-4ea4-821c-5ab733066e53","type":"text"},